;What matters to me is that the charter school movement is laying the groundwork for creating a competitive environment for the running of publicly funded schools. I believe that, in time, we will see dramatic improvements in charter schools because of three components: &#10;1) Greater local control&#10;2) Competitive pressure on school administrators&#10;3) Expectations of innovation&#10;It may take a couple more decades before charter schools leave public schools behind, but I believe they will do so. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="792" language="en" documentId="4795" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Captain Chaos" date="7th November 2006 05:05 PM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.volconvo.com/forums/showthread.php?t=12481&amp;page=6" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4795" notes="" title="Public Schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="83"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="84" end="299"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="300" end="570"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="571" end="595"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="596" end="644"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="645" end="674"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="675" end="792"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59 63"/></xmi:XMI>